library(mgcv)
library(ggplot2)

regDat <- readr::read_csv("regDat.csv")

estDat <- readr::read_csv("estDat.csv")

regObj <- gam(log10(Flow.y) ~ s(log10(Flow.x), bs = "ts"), data = regDat, select = TRUE)

getGamIntervals <- function(gamObj, estDF, convert = TRUE) {
  newCov <- vcov(regObj)
  pred <- predict(regObj, estDat, se.fit = TRUE)
  se.fit <- pred$se.fit
  set.seed(42); N <- 10000
  theDiff <- rmvn(N, mu = rep(0, nrow(newCov)), V = newCov)
  newMat <- predict(regObj, estDat, type = "lpmatrix")
  simMat <- newMat %*% t(theDiff)
  absMat <- abs(sweep(simMat, 1, se.fit, FUN = "/"))
  masVec <- apply(absMat, 2L, max)
  crit <- quantile(masVec, prob = 0.95, type = 8)
  pred <- transform(cbind(data.frame(estDat), pred),
                    uprP = fit + (2 * se.fit),
                    lwrP = fit - (2 * se.fit),
                    uprS = fit + (crit * se.fit),
                    lwrS = fit - (crit * se.fit))
  if(convert == TRUE) {
    pred$fit <- 10^pred$fit
    pred$uprP <- 10^pred$uprP      
    pred$lwrP <- 10^pred$lwrP      
    pred$uprS <- 10^pred$uprS      
    pred$lwrS <- 10^pred$lwrS
  }
  pred$fit <- signif(pred$fit, 3)
  pred$uprP <- signif(pred$uprP, 3)
  pred$lwrP <- signif(pred$lwrP, 3)
  pred$uprS <- signif(pred$uprS, 3)
  pred$lwrS <- signif(pred$lwrS, 3)
  return(pred)
}

pred <- getGamIntervals(regObj, estDat, convert = TRUE)

p <- ggplot(data = pred, aes(x = dateTime, y = fit)) +
  geom_line(color = "blue") +
  geom_line(data = pred, aes(x = dateTime, y = uprP), linetype = "dotted") +
  geom_line(data = pred, aes(x = dateTime, y = lwrP), linetype = "dotted") +
  geom_line(data = pred, aes(x = dateTime, y = uprS), linetype = "dashed") +
  geom_line(data = pred, aes(x = dateTime, y = lwrS), linetype = "dashed") +
  theme_bw()
  
p

"gamIntervals" <-
  function(gam_predicts_wsefit, gam=NULL,
           interval=c("none", "confidence", "prediction"), level=0.95, ...) {
    # Demo: X <- 2*pi*(1:360)/360 # simulate some X
    #       Y <- 1.6*sin(X) + 40*cos(X) + rnorm(length(X), sd=12)
    #     GAM <- gam(Y~s(X)); PGAM <- predict(GAM, se.fit=TRUE)
    #     PGAM <- gamIntervals(PGAM, gam=GAM)
    #     print(head(PGAM))
    # plot(GAM$hat, (PGAM$se.fit/PGAM$residual.scale)^2)
    # Compare what the GAM says its leverage values are to back computed.
    # The plot() only works because predict() called back on the actuall model.
    if(class(gam)[1] != "gam") {
      warning("need the actual GAM model too via the 'gam' argument")
      return()
    }
    z <- as.data.frame(gam_predicts_wsefit)
    if(! any(names(z) == "se.fit")) {
      warning("need gam predictions with se.fit=TRUE passed for 'z'")
      return()
    }
    interval <- match.arg(interval)
    sum.gam <- summary(gam); n <- sum.gam$n # summary.gam() and the sample size
    z$residual.scale <- sigma <- sqrt(sum.gam$scale) # residual standard error
    df <- n-sum(gam$edf)           # total degrees of freedom
    QT <- abs(qt((1-level)/2, df)) # will do the +/- separately
    if(interval == "none") {
      z$lwr <- z$upr <- NA
    } else {
      one <- ifelse(interval == "confidence", 0, 1)
      tmp <- sqrt(one+(z$se.fit/sigma)^2)
      z$lwr <- z$fit - sigma*QT*tmp
      z$upr <- z$fit + sigma*QT*tmp
    }
    z <- z[,c(4,1,5,2,3)]
    attr(z, "interval")                  <- interval
    attr(z, "level")                     <- level
    attr(z, "t-dist_degrees_of_freedom") <- df
    return(z)
  }

regObjPred <- predict(regObj, estDat, se.fit = TRUE)

newPred <- gamIntervals(regObjPred, regObj, interval = "confidence")

newPred2 <- gamIntervals(regObjPred, regObj, interval = "prediction")

newPred[,c(1,2,3)] <- 10^newPred[,c(1,2,3)]

newPred2[,c(1,2,3)] <- 10^newPred2[,c(1,2,3)]

colnames(newPred) <- paste0(colnames(newPred), ".new")

colnames(newPred2) <- paste0(colnames(newPred2), ".new2")

pred <- dplyr::bind_cols(pred, newPred, newPred2)

p <- p +
  geom_line(data = pred, aes(x = dateTime, y = lwr.new), linetype = "longdash") +
  geom_line(data = pred, aes(x = dateTime, y = upr.new), linetype = "longdash") +
  geom_line(data = pred, aes(x = dateTime, y = lwr.new2), linetype = "longdash") +
  geom_line(data = pred, aes(x = dateTime, y = upr.new2), linetype = "longdash") +
  geom_line(data = pred, aes(x = dateTime, y = fit.new2), color = "red")
  
p
